{
  "stem": "26140.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the SS, more or less, weren't so much in-- in the visibility as the Ukrainian guards.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all I did hear is every morning, the Rapportfuhrer, the one who made the appels, used to shout through a microphone, all SS men must move from the camp outside.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every time that was repeated, because sometimes the SS used to wander about.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that is the only thing I do remember, that they tried to get them out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One year, approximately, maybe three quarter of a year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we've seen the American arrive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they try to give everybody chocolate and friendly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We moved right away outside the German blocks where the SS were accommodated to see if we can find any food or whatever.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember I found some wine there, which I took.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they improved the food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They gave us a lot better food, since the American came, which was rather disastrous.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because, when you were fed for three or so many years with a very thin food, when you got fatty soup and so on, a lot of people did die from stomach troubles, because the stomach couldn't stand that much food all-- all-- all the sudden.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that was one of the things which I thought the Americans didn't do right.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother was also in Buchenwald, and my twin brother was moved to different camp, which was in-- later on occupied by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he returned back to Poland, because being occupied by Russian, you had no other choice.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was-- came to Auschwitz about 1941.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was put there because he belonged to a-- a underground organization of officers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was moved to Auschwitz, and later on, transferred to-- to Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
